node.text:
For today's walkthrough, here's our 20 ft. Homestead build for your enjoyment!

Want some nerdy specs? Here you go:

Specifications

Trailer: 20 ft. Trailer Made Custom Tiny Home Trailer Foundation
​Model: Mohican
Cost: Starting at $69,000
Exterior Siding: LP Vertical Smart Siding - 60 Year Warranty (With Aluminum Accent Panel)
Roof: Steel Roof - 40 Year Warranty
Exterior Storage Box: Included
Flooring: Luxury Vinyl Plank (LVP) Flooring
Interior Walls: Poplar Tongue & Groove
Hardware Package: Brushed Nickel Hardware Package
Social Area: Custom Bookcase & Open Space for Customer-Provided Furniture
Closet: Custom Shelving & Hanging Clothes Closet
Sleeping: Large King Loft
Stairs: Custom Staircase w/Built-In Storage

Kitchen

Cabinetry: Custom Cabinetry 
Backsplash: None
Countertops: Butcher Block
Sink: 30 In. Stainless Steel Undermount Sink
Oven/Range: None (Customer Provided)
Refrigerator: Apartment-Sized Stainless Steel Refrigerator
Microwave: None (Customer Provided)

Bathroom

Shower: Fiberglass Shower
Toilet: Nature's Head Composting Toilet
Shelving: Floating Shelves
Sink: None
Door: Custom Sliding Barn Door

Water/Heat/Insulation/Power

Heat/AC: Ductless Mini Split
Water Heater: Gas Propane Water Heater (PrecisionTemp)
Electric Service: 50 Amp Service w/Hybrid Power System for Solar
Insulation: Closed Cell Spray Foam Insulation: 3" In Walls/Ceilings, 4" In Floors

Like specifications like these? You can review all of the specs on our homes at www.moderntinyliving.com!

Niagara, a 24 ft. tiny house based upon our Kokosing model, is today's glorious Walkthrough Wednsday!

If you've not enjoyed this beautiful home, take the next 2 minutes and give it look. Niagara features all of the amenities and features that make our Kokosing line one of the most popular modes in the world, but also includes a few design elements that really make it stick out. The extended work desk, for example, is a cusotm element that really make the home more usable for its owner.

Enjoy!

For this week's Walkthrough Wednesday, let's take a stroll through our 20 ft. Cocoa build, a variation of our size and budget-friendly Mohican model. Featuring a full kitchen, full bath, king loft, sleeper couch, clothes storage area and all the incredible craftwork of all MTL homes, Cocoa is a perfect home for a weekend getaway or travel home.

Want details on pricing, timelines or have other questions? Email us directly at contact@moderntinyliving.com.

node.text:
Today's Walkthrough comes courtesy of our most recently completed home, the spectacular 28 ft. tiny house on wheels, The Bison!

We dropped the photo album for The Bison last week, but there's nothing like a video walkthrough to get a feel for the overall livability of the tiny house.

The Bison was architecturally designed and built by Modern Tiny Living in Columbus, Ohio. We ship nationwide, and we're ready to rock n' roll.

Check out the entire photo album at www.moderntinyliving.com/the-bison

It's Walkthrough Wednesday!

This week's walkthrough comes to you on behalf of Serenity. Serenity is a 28 ft. custom tiny house on wheels by Modern Tiny Living. We shared the kitchen yesterday and figured it was high-time that we re-share the video walkthrough from last year!

Serenity is built similarly to one of our Point models, however it is extended 8 full feet, allowing for a much larger MTL social area as well as a full office suite in the rear of the unit (which includes its own entrance/exit).

Learn more at www.moderntinyliving.com/serenity

Specifications

​Model: Mohican
Cost: Starting at $69,000
Exterior Siding: LP Vertical Smart Siding - 60 Year Warranty (With Aluminum Accent Panel)
Roof: Steel Roof - 40 Year Warranty
Exterior Storage Box: Included
Flooring: Luxury Vinyl Plank (LVP) Flooring
Interior Walls: Poplar Tongue & Groove
Hardware Package: Brushed Nickel Hardware Package
Social Area: Custom Bookcase & Open Space for Customer-Provided Furniture
Closet: Custom Shelving & Hanging Clothes Closet
Sleeping: Large King Loft
Stairs: Custom Staircase w/Built-In Storage

Kitchen

Cabinetry: Custom Cabinetry 
Backsplash: None
Countertops: Butcher Block
Sink: 30 In. Stainless Steel Undermount Sink
Oven/Range: None (Customer Provided)
Refrigerator: Apartment-Sized Stainless Steel Refrigerator
Microwave: None (Customer Provided)

Bathroom

Shower: Fiberglass Shower
Toilet: Nature's Head Composting Toilet
Shelving: Floating Shelves
Sink: None
Door: Custom Sliding Barn Door

Water/Heat/Insulation/Power

Heat/AC: Ductless Mini Split

Electric Service: 50 Amp Service w/Hybrid Power System for Solar
Insulation: Closed Cell Spray Foam Insulation: 3" In Walls/Ceilings, 4" In Floors

Like specifications like these? You can review all of the specs on our homes at www.moderntinyliving.com!

Just head to our website, go to Galleries, and click The Bison!

The Bison features two king lofts (one with skylights), a custom honey-combed tiled corner for a wood-burning stove, a jaw-dropping custom full kitchen with all the appliances (including oven), huge closet, full bath, washer/dryer hookups, and much more. It is a truly complete home, and a stunning example of just how functional and livable a tiny home can truly be when done right.

It's been a little while since we shamelessly gloated about the multi-talented Modern Tiny Living Social Area, so let's head on over to our Rivendell build to showcase the glory. We custom-build every single MTL Social Area to be a true swiss army knife of a space for our tiny house customers.

First, you'll notice the elevated MTL Social Area features gobs of storage, including subfloor storage that is perfect for those winter clothes, collectibles, books, or that stuff that you just CAN'T get rid of (even though you know Marie Kondo would tell you to). 

Second, there are drawers everywhere. 8 in total. Stash your clothes here, or other goodies.

Last but not least, this couch is comfortable as heck, and it turns into an extra comfortable bed, too. Function, beauty, storage, snoozing, hanging out - the MTL Social Area has it all, folks.

It's Manteo Monday!

Manteo is a beautiful variation of our Point model, and features a very simple layout with beautiful, budget-friendly, features. Less windows, a non-elevated social, and stowable plug-in appliances save on cost, but don’t worry, it still has a beautiful full bath and king loft. Everything you need without the fuss!

Starting around $69,000, Manteo won't break the bank (compared to other tiny homes at least), and its robust build quality will last for years and years. No, it's not a deluxe $150,000 tiny house castle, but it is an easily-towed roadworthy companion made to last - and make memories forever.

Learn more at www.moderntinyliving.com/manteo 👈
